There was no armed resistance against the legitimate government, because the rule of the Russian Empire in Georgia did not have any legal basis, including the most important argument of the Russian Empire - the treaties of subordination signed by the Kingdom-principalities of Georgia.  2. There was no uprising of peasants and confrontation between social strata, because all social strata of the population of Georgia were involved in these events, such as serfs
